Burgess constructed her own legend and how the town of Sandwich embraced that history as its own. Through careful analysis of myriad primary sources, Shockley also addresses how Burgess dealt with the conflicting gender roles of her life, reconciling her traditionally masculine adventures at sea and her independent lifestyle with the accepted ideals of the period’s “Victorian woman.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aAutobiographyxWomen authorsvCase studies. 0aMiddle class womenzMassachusettszSandwichvBiography. 0aSeafaring lifezMassachusettszSandwichxHistoryy19th centuryvSources. 0aShip captains' spouseszMassachusettszSandwichvBiography. 0aWomenxIdentityvCase studies. 0aWomenzMassachusettszSandwichvBiography. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / New England (CT, MA, ME, NH, RI, VT).2bisacsh  a1852.  a1856.  a1917.  a22-year-old.  aBurgess.  aCaptains.  aChallenger.  aCrowell.  aHannah.  aMassachusetts.  aMegan.  aRebecca.  aSandwich.  aShockley.  aTaylor.  aWidow.  aWilliam.  aWithin.  acaptain.  aconstructed.  acrossed.  adied.  adying.  adysentery.  aeleven.  aembraced.  aequator.  aexamines.  afamilys.  afrom.  ahistory.  ahome.  ahusband.  alearned.  alegend.  amarriage.  amarried.  anavigate.  aown.  aproposals.  arefused.  areturned.  asail.  asaved.  aship.  athat.  athree.  atimes.  atown.  avessel.  awealthy.  awhere.  ayears.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814786529423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814786529.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aE